<section id="gpgsign"
         xreflabel="gpgsign">
  <title>
  GPGsign
  </title>

  <section>
    <title>
    Definition
    </title>

    <para>
    Directs SystemStudio to sign the system distribution's packages with the specified GPG
    key.
    </para>

    <para>
    This module is a member of the <emphasis role="strong">repocreate</emphasis>
    module group.
    </para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Syntax
    </title>

    <programlisting>
[&lt;gpgsign [enabled=BOOLEAN]&gt;
   &lt;public-key&gt;PATH&lt;/public-key&gt;
   &lt;secret-key&gt;PATH&lt;/secret-key&gt;
  [&lt;passphrase&gt;TEXT&lt;/passphrase&gt;]
 &lt;/gpgsign&gt;]
    </programlisting>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Attributes
    </title>

    <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
      enabled
      </term>

      <listitem>
      <para>
      See Common Attribute <emphasis><xref linkend="enabled" /></emphasis>.
      </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Elements
    </title>

    <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
      passphrase
      </term>

      <listitem>
      <para>
      The GPG secret key's passphrase; used when accessing the secret key
      in order to perform the signing process. If
      <emphasis>gpgsign/passphrase</emphasis> is not present, the user is
      prompted on the command line for the passphrase to use.
      </para>

      <note>
      <para>
      Remember that if the passphrase is stored in the system distribution file, anyone
      with read access to the file can retrieve it. Be sure to take the
      appropriate steps, whether by limiting read access to the system distribution
      file or entering the passphrase at the prompt.
      </para>
      </note>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>
      public-key
      </term>

      <listitem>
      <para>
      The <varname>PATH</varname> to the exported, armored GPG public key
      that corresponds to the secret key used to sign the packages in this
      system distribution.
      </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>
      secret-key
      </term>

      <listitem>
      <para>
      The <varname>PATH</varname> to the exported, armored GPG secret key
      with which to sign system packages.
      </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Examples
    </title>

    <informalexample>
    <programlisting>
&lt;gpgsign enabled="true"&gt;
  &lt;public-key&gt;GPG/GPG-public.key&lt;/public-key&gt;
  &lt;secret-key&gt;GPG/GPG-secret.key&lt;/secret-key&gt;
  &lt;passphrase&gt;secret&lt;/passphrase&gt;
&lt;/gpgsign&gt;
    </programlisting>
    </informalexample>
  </section>

